  "text": "Found all consumer group partition assignment strategy implementations in apache/kafka (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489). The repository contains two main implementations: client-side assignors in the 'clients' module and server-side assignors in the 'group-coordinator' module.\n\nClient-side implementations (in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/):\n- RangeAssignor.java: Implements range-based partition assignment, extends AbstractPartitionAssignor. Assigns contiguous partition ranges to consumers on a per-topic basis.\n- RoundRobinAssignor.java: Implements round-robin partition assignment, extends AbstractPartitionAssignor. Distributes partitions to consumers in a round-robin fashion across all topics.\n- StickyAssignor.java: Implements sticky assignment strategy, extends AbstractStickyAssignor. Attempts to preserve partition assignments while maintaining balance.\n- CooperativeStickyAssignor.java: Implements cooperative version of sticky assignment, extends AbstractStickyAssignor. Allows cooperative rebalancing as opposed to eager rebalancing.\n\nBase classes (in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/):\n- AbstractPartitionAssignor.java: Abstract base class implementing ConsumerPartitionAssignor interface. Provides common functionality for partition assignment including rack-aware assignment logic.\n- AbstractStickyAssignor.java: Abstract base class extending AbstractPartitionAssignor. Provides shared sticky assignment implementation used by both StickyAssignor and CooperativeStickyAssignor.\n\nServer-side implementation (in group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/assignor/):\n- RangeAssignor.java: Server-side range assignor implementing ConsumerGroupPartitionAssignor interface. Used by the group coordinator for server-side assignment in the modern consumer protocol."
